{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"To be new at TED -- it's like being the last high-school virgin."},{"time":6000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":8000,"text":"You know that all of the cool people are -- they're doing it."},{"time":12000,"text":"And you're on the outside, you're at home."},{"time":14000,"text":"You're like the Raspyni Brothers,"},{"time":16000,"text":"where you've got your balls in cold water. And --"},{"time":20000,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":22000,"text":"you just play with your fingers all day. And then you get invited."},{"time":27000,"text":"And you're on the inside, and it's everything you hoped it would be."},{"time":33000,"text":"It's exciting and there's music playing all of the time"},{"time":36000,"text":"and then suddenly it's over. And it's only taken five minutes."},{"time":40000,"text":"And you want to go back and do it again."},{"time":43000,"text":"But I really appreciate being here. And thank you, Chris,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and also, thank you, Deborah Patton, for making this possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"So anyway, today we'll talk about architecture a little bit,"},{"time":55000,"text":"within the subject of creation and optimism."},{"time":59000,"text":"And if you put creation and optimism together,"},{"time":62000,"text":"you've got two choices that you can talk about."},{"time":64000,"text":"You can talk about creationism --"},{"time":67000,"text":"which I think wouldn't go down well with this audience,"},{"time":69000,"text":"at least not from a view where you were a proponent of it --"},{"time":72000,"text":"or you can talk about optimisations, spelled the British way, with an S, instead of a Z."},{"time":78000,"text":"And I think that's what I'd like to talk about today."},{"time":80000,"text":"But any kind of conversation about architecture --"},{"time":85000,"text":"which is, in fact, what you were just talking about, what was going on here,"},{"time":88000,"text":"setting up TED, small-scale architecture --"},{"time":90000,"text":"at the present time can't really happen without a conversation about this,"},{"time":98000,"text":"the World Trade Center, and what's been going on there, what it means to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"Because if architecture is what I believe it to be,"},{"time":109000,"text":"which is the built form of our cultural ambitions,"},{"time":113000,"text":"what do you do when presented with an opportunity to rectify a situation"},{"time":121000,"text":"that represents somebody else's cultural ambitions relative to us?"},{"time":126000,"text":"And our own opportunity to make something new there?"},{"time":131000,"text":"This has been a really galvanizing issue for a long time."},{"time":135000,"text":"I think that the World Trade Center in, rather an unfortunate way,"},{"time":139000,"text":"brought architecture into focus"},{"time":141000,"text":"in a way that I don't think people had thought of in a long time,"},{"time":143000,"text":"and made it a subject for common conversation."},{"time":146000,"text":"I don't remember, in my 20-year career of practicing and writing about architecture,"},{"time":150000,"text":"a time when five people sat me down at a table"},{"time":152000,"text":"and asked me very serious questions about zoning, fire exiting,"},{"time":158000,"text":"safety concerns and whether carpet burns."},{"time":161000,"text":"These are just not things we talked about very often."},{"time":165000,"text":"And yet, now, it's talked about all the time."},{"time":167000,"text":"At the point where you can weaponize your buildings,"},{"time":172000,"text":"you have to suddenly think about architecture in a very different way."},{"time":175000,"text":"And so now we're going to think about architecture in a very different way,"},{"time":180000,"text":"we're going to think about it like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"How many of you saw USA Today, today? There it is. Looks like that."},{"time":187000,"text":"There's the World Trade Center site, on the front cover."},{"time":189000,"text":"They've made a selection."},{"time":191000,"text":"They've chosen a project by Daniel Libeskind,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the enfant terrible of the moment of architecture."},{"time":198000,"text":"Child-prodigy piano player, he started on the squeezebox,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and moved to a little more serious issue, a bigger instrument,"},{"time":204000,"text":"and now to an even larger instrument,"},{"time":206000,"text":"upon which to work his particular brand of deconstructivist magic,"},{"time":212000,"text":"as you see here."},{"time":214000,"text":"He was one of six people who were invited to participate in this competition,"},{"time":217000,"text":"after six previous firms struck out"},{"time":222000,"text":"with things that were so stupid and banal"},{"time":224000,"text":"that even the city of New York was forced to go,"},{"time":226000,"text":"\"Oh, I'm really sorry, we screwed up.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"Right. Can we do this again from the top,"},{"time":232000,"text":"except use some people with a vague hint of talent,"},{"time":234000,"text":"instead of just six utter boobs like we brought in last time,"},{"time":239000,"text":"real estate hacks of the kind who usually plan our cities."},{"time":242000,"text":"Let's bring in some real architects for a change."},{"time":244000,"text":"And so we got this, or we had a choice of that. Oh, stop clapping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"It's too late. That is gone."},{"time":256000,"text":"This was a scheme by a team called THINK, a New York-based team,"},{"time":259000,"text":"and then there was that one, which was the Libeskind scheme."},{"time":262000,"text":"This one, this is going to be the new World Trade Center:"},{"time":266000,"text":"a giant hole in the ground with big buildings falling into it."},{"time":270000,"text":"Now, I don't know what you think, but I think this is a pretty stupid decision,"},{"time":274000,"text":"because what you've done is just made a permanent memorial to destruction"},{"time":279000,"text":"by making it look like the destruction is going to continue forever."},{"time":283000,"text":"But that's what we're going to do."},{"time":285000,"text":"But I want you to think about these things"},{"time":288000,"text":"in terms of a kind of ongoing struggle that American architecture represents,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and that these two things talk about very specifically."},{"time":294000,"text":"And that is the wild divergence in how we choose our architects,"},{"time":299000,"text":"in trying to decide whether we want architecture"},{"time":302000,"text":"from the kind of technocratic solution to everything --"},{"time":305000,"text":"that there is a large, technical answer that can solve all problems,"},{"time":310000,"text":"be they social, be they physical, be they chemical --"},{"time":314000,"text":"or something that's more of a romantic solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"Now, I don't mean romantic as in, this is a nice place to take someone on a date."},{"time":321000,"text":"I mean romantic in the sense of, there are things larger and grander than us."},{"time":327000,"text":"So, in the American tradition,"},{"time":329000,"text":"the difference between the technocratic and the romantic,"},{"time":331000,"text":"would be the difference between Thomas Jefferson's"},{"time":334000,"text":"Cartesian grids spreading across the United States,"},{"time":337000,"text":"that gives us basically the whole shape"},{"time":340000,"text":"of every western state in the United States,"},{"time":342000,"text":"as a really, truly, technocratic solution, a bowing to the --"},{"time":348000,"text":"in Jefferson's time -- current, popular philosophy of rationalism."},{"time":354000,"text":"Or the way we went to describe that later: manifest destiny."},{"time":361000,"text":"Now, which would you rather be? A grid, or manifest destiny?"},{"time":366000,"text":"Manifest destiny."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"It's a big deal. It sounds big, it sounds important,"},{"time":373000,"text":"it sounds solid. It sounds American. Ballsy, serious, male."},{"time":379000,"text":"And that kind of fight has gone on back and forth in architecture all the time."},{"time":384000,"text":"I mean, it goes on in our private lives, too, every single day."},{"time":387000,"text":"We all want to go out and buy an Audi TT, don't we?"},{"time":390000,"text":"Everyone here must own one, or at least they craved one"},{"time":393000,"text":"the moment they saw one."},{"time":395000,"text":"And then they hopped in it, turned the little electronic key,"},{"time":397000,"text":"rather than the real key, zipped home on their new superhighway,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and drove straight into a garage that looks like a Tudor castle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"Why? Why? Why do you want to do that?"},{"time":412000,"text":"Why do we all want to do that? I even owned a Tudor thing once myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"It's in our nature to go ricocheting"},{"time":421000,"text":"back and forth between this technocratic solution"},{"time":426000,"text":"and a larger, sort of more romantic image of where we are."},{"time":429000,"text":"So we're going to go straight into this."},{"time":431000,"text":"Can I have the lights off for a moment?"},{"time":433000,"text":"I'm going to talk about two architects very, very briefly"},{"time":436000,"text":"that represent the current split, architecturally,"},{"time":438000,"text":"between these two traditions of a technocratic"},{"time":440000,"text":"or technological solution and a romantic solution."},{"time":444000,"text":"And these are two of the top architectural practices in the United States today."},{"time":447000,"text":"One very young, one a little more mature."},{"time":449000,"text":"This is the work of a firm called SHoP,"},{"time":451000,"text":"and what you're seeing here, is their isometric drawings"},{"time":455000,"text":"of what will be a large-scale camera obscura in a public park."},{"time":459000,"text":"Does everybody know what a camera obscura is?"},{"time":462000,"text":"Yeah, it's one of those giant camera lenses"},{"time":464000,"text":"that takes a picture of the outside world --"},{"time":466000,"text":"it's sort of a little movie, without any moving parts --"},{"time":469000,"text":"and projects it on a page, and you can see the world outside you as you walk around it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473000,"text":"This is just the outline of it, and you can see,"},{"time":476000,"text":"does it look like a regular building? No."},{"time":478000,"text":"It's actually non-orthogonal: it's not up and down,"},{"time":480000,"text":"square, rectangular, anything like that,"},{"time":482000,"text":"that you'd see in a normal shape of a building."},{"time":484000,"text":"The computer revolution, the technocratic, technological revolution,"},{"time":487000,"text":"has allowed us to jettison normal-shaped buildings,"},{"time":490000,"text":"traditionally shaped buildings, in favor of non-orthogonal buildings such as this."},{"time":494000,"text":"What's interesting about it is not the shape."},{"time":496000,"text":"What's interesting about it is how it's made. How it's made."},{"time":500000,"text":"A brand-new way to put buildings together,"},{"time":502000,"text":"something called mass customization. No, it is not an oxymoron."},{"time":505000,"text":"What makes the building expensive, in the traditional sense,"},{"time":508000,"text":"is making individual parts custom, that you can't do over and over again."},{"time":511000,"text":"That's why we all live in developer houses."},{"time":513000,"text":"They all want to save money by building the same thing 500 times."},{"time":517000,"text":"That's because it's cheaper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"Mass customization works by an architect feeding into a computer,"},{"time":523000,"text":"a program that says, manufacture these parts."},{"time":526000,"text":"The computer then talks to a machine --"},{"time":528000,"text":"a computer-operated machine, a cad-cam machine --"},{"time":532000,"text":"that can make a zillion different changes, at a moment's notice,"},{"time":535000,"text":"because the computer is just a machine."},{"time":537000,"text":"It doesn't care. It's manufacturing the parts."},{"time":540000,"text":"It doesn't see any excess cost. It doesn't spend any extra time."},{"time":543000,"text":"It's not a laborer -- it's simply an electronic lathe,"},{"time":547000,"text":"so the parts can all be cut at the same time."},{"time":549000,"text":"Meanwhile, instead of sending someone working drawings,"},{"time":552000,"text":"which are those huge sets of blueprints that you've seen your whole life,"},{"time":555000,"text":"what the architect can do is send a set of assembly instructions,"},{"time":560000,"text":"like you used to get when you were a child,"},{"time":562000,"text":"when you bought little models that said, \"Bolt A to B, and C to D.\""},{"time":566000,"text":"And so what the builder will get is every single individual part"},{"time":570000,"text":"that has been custom manufactured off-site and delivered on a truck"},{"time":574000,"text":"to the site, to that builder, and a set of these instruction manuals."},{"time":578000,"text":"Just simple \"Bolt A to B\" and they will be able to put them together."},{"time":581000,"text":"Here's the little drawing that tells them how that works --"},{"time":584000,"text":"and that's what will happen in the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"You're underneath it, looking up into the lens of the camera obscura."},{"time":589000,"text":"Lest you think this is all fiction, lest you think this is all fantasy, or romance,"},{"time":594000,"text":"these same architects were asked to produce something"},{"time":597000,"text":"for the central courtyard of PS1, which is a museum in Brooklyn, New York,"},{"time":601000,"text":"as part of their young architects summer series."},{"time":603000,"text":"And they said, well, it's summer, what do you do?"},{"time":605000,"text":"In the summer, you go to the beach."},{"time":607000,"text":"And when you go to the beach, what do you get? You get sand dunes."},{"time":609000,"text":"So let's make architectural sand dunes and a beach cabana."},{"time":612000,"text":"So they went out and they modeled a computer model of a sand dune."},{"time":616000,"text":"They took photographs, they fed the photographs into their computer program,"},{"time":619000,"text":"and that computer program shaped a sand dune"},{"time":623000,"text":"and then took that sand dune shape and turned it into --"},{"time":626000,"text":"at their instructions, using standard software with slight modifications --"},{"time":630000,"text":"a set of instructions for pieces of wood."},{"time":633000,"text":"And those are the pieces of wood. Those are the instructions."},{"time":635000,"text":"These are the pieces, and here's a little of that blown up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"What you can see is there's about six different colors,"},{"time":640000,"text":"and each color represents a type of wood to be cut, a piece of wood to be cut."},{"time":644000,"text":"All of which were delivered by flat bed, on a truck,"},{"time":647000,"text":"and hand assembled in 48 hours by a team of eight people,"},{"time":653000,"text":"only one of whom had ever seen the plans before."},{"time":656000,"text":"Only one of whom had ever seen the plans before."},{"time":659000,"text":"And here comes dune-scape, coming up out of the courtyard,"},{"time":662000,"text":"and there it is fully built."},{"time":665000,"text":"There are only 16 different pieces of wood,"},{"time":669000,"text":"only 16 different assembly parts here."},{"time":672000,"text":"Looks like a beautiful piano sounding board on the inside."},{"time":675000,"text":"It has its own built-in swimming pool, very, very cool."},{"time":679000,"text":"It's a great place for parties -- it was, it was only up for six weeks."},{"time":684000,"text":"It's got little dressing rooms and cabanas,"},{"time":687000,"text":"where lots of interesting things went on, all summer long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"Now, lest you think that this is only for the light at heart, or just temporary installations,"},{"time":697000,"text":"this is the same firm working at the World Trade Center,"},{"time":700000,"text":"replacing the bridge that used to go across West Street,"},{"time":704000,"text":"that very important pedestrian connection"},{"time":706000,"text":"between the city of New York and the redevelopment of the West Side."},{"time":712000,"text":"They were asked to design, replace that bridge in six weeks,"},{"time":715000,"text":"building it, including all of the parts, manufactured."},{"time":719000,"text":"And they were able to do it. That was their design,"},{"time":721000,"text":"using that same computer modeling system"},{"time":723000,"text":"and only five or six really different kinds of parts,"},{"time":726000,"text":"a couple of struts, like this, some exterior cladding material"},{"time":730000,"text":"and a very simple framing system"},{"time":732000,"text":"that was all manufactured off-site and delivered by truck."},{"time":734000,"text":"They were able to create that."},{"time":737000,"text":"They were able to create something wonderful."},{"time":739000,"text":"They're now building a 16-story building on the side of New York,"},{"time":742000,"text":"using the same technology."},{"time":744000,"text":"Here we're going to walk across the bridge at night."},{"time":746000,"text":"It's self-lit, you don't need any overhead lighting,"},{"time":748000,"text":"so the neighbors don't complain about metal-halide lighting in their face."},{"time":751000,"text":"Here it is going across. And there, down the other side,"},{"time":754000,"text":"and you get the same kind of grandeur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756000,"text":"Now, let me show you, quickly, the opposite, if I may."},{"time":760000,"text":"Woo, pretty, huh. This is the other side of the coin."},{"time":763000,"text":"This is the work of David Rockwell from New York City,"},{"time":766000,"text":"whose work you can see out here today."},{"time":768000,"text":"The current king of the romantics, who approaches his work"},{"time":771000,"text":"in a very different fashion."},{"time":773000,"text":"It's not to create a technological solution, it's to seduce you"},{"time":776000,"text":"into something that you can do, into something that will please you,"},{"time":780000,"text":"something that will lift your spirits,"},{"time":782000,"text":"something that will make you feel as if are in another world --"},{"time":785000,"text":"such as his Nobu restaurant in New York,"},{"time":788000,"text":"which is supposed to take you from the clutter of New York City"},{"time":792000,"text":"to the simplicity of Japan and the elegance of Japanese tradition."},{"time":797000,"text":"\"When it's all said and done, it's got to look like seaweed,\" said the owner."},{"time":802000,"text":"Or his restaurant, Pod, in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"I want you to know the room you're looking at is stark white."},{"time":809000,"text":"Every single surface of this restaurant is white."},{"time":812000,"text":"The reason it has so much color is that it changes using lighting."},{"time":817000,"text":"It's all about sensuality. It's all about transforming."},{"time":821000,"text":"Watch this -- I'm not touching any buttons, ladies and gentlemen."},{"time":824000,"text":"This is happening by itself."},{"time":826000,"text":"It transforms through the magic of lighting."},{"time":828000,"text":"It's all about sensuality. It's all about touch."},{"time":831000,"text":"Rosa Mexicano restaurant, where he transports us to the shores of Acapulco,"},{"time":836000,"text":"up on the Upper West Side,"},{"time":838000,"text":"with this wall of cliff divers who -- there you go, like that."},{"time":843000,"text":"Let's see it one more time."},{"time":845000,"text":"Okay, just to make sure that you've enjoyed it."},{"time":848000,"text":"And finally, it's about comfort, it's about making you feel good"},{"time":852000,"text":"in places that you wouldn't have felt good before."},{"time":854000,"text":"It's about bringing nature to the inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"In the Guardian Tower of New York, converted to a W Union Square --"},{"time":860000,"text":"I'm sorry I'm rushing -- where we had to bring in the best horticulturists in the world"},{"time":865000,"text":"to make sure that the interior of this dragged the garden space"},{"time":868000,"text":"of the court garden of the Union Square into the building itself."},{"time":872000,"text":"It's about stimulation."},{"time":876000,"text":"This is a wine-buying experience simplified by color and taste."},{"time":881000,"text":"Fizzy, fresh, soft, luscious, juicy, smooth, big and sweet wines,"},{"time":885000,"text":"all explained to you by color and texture on the wall."},{"time":889000,"text":"And finally, it's about entertainment, as in his headquarters"},{"time":893000,"text":"for the Cirque du Soleil, Orlando, Florida,"},{"time":895000,"text":"where you're asked to enter the Greek theater,"},{"time":897000,"text":"look under the tent and join the magic world of Cirque du Soleil."},{"time":900000,"text":"And I think I'll probably leave it at that. Thank you very much."}]}]}